title: One person arrested after New Mexico motorcycle rally shooting that left 3 dead, at least 5 injured
description: Three people were killed and at least five were injured — including one who has been charged with murder — in a shooting Saturday during a popular motorcycle rally at a New Mexico resort town, according to officials.

title: Inside the Florida group pushing to slash food stamp rolls nationwide
description: Debt ceiling negotiators on Capitol Hill have agreed to tighten work requirements for SNAP benefits a longtime conservative goal that the low-profile FGA has been pushing at the state level.

title: Turkey's Erdogan appears set to hold on to power after presidential run-off vote
description: ISTANBUL — Turkey's president, Recep Tayyip Erdoğan, appears set to extend his leadership of the influential NATO member after seeing the strongest challenge to his 20-year rule.

title: 'Succession' extras kept spoilers a secret for months. Now they're sharing their stories on TikTok.
description: Extras who appeared in 'Succession' share what it was like to be on set for pivotal scenes and how they stayed mum on spoilers.

title: Kyiv hit by massive Russian drone attack as city marks its founding
description: Ahead of the anniversary of its founding in 482 A.D., Kyiv suffered the largest drone attack since the start of the war with Russia, Ukrainian officials said Sunday.

title: Erdoğan looks to extend his 20-year rule as Turkey votes in presidential run-off
description: ANKARA, Turkey — It’s one of the most hotly contested presidential elections in recent times, but at the Arjantin İlkokulu elementary school in Turkey’s capital Ankara, the mood was quiet, orderly and calm.

title: Biden hopes to get re-elected with a little help from his friends
description: President Joe Biden is planning to tap an expansive stable of friends and allies to go where he can’t, say what he won’t, and be what he’ll never be.

title: Man pleads not guilty to human smuggling case at U.S.-Canada border near where 4 died
description: A Florida man who was arrested last year near the U.S.-Canada border with two migrants in a rented passenger van pleaded not guilty Friday to federal human smuggling charges.

title: McCarthy says House will vote on Wednesday to raise the debt ceiling
description: House Speaker Kevin McCarthy said the text of the debt ceiling agreement will be available to lawmakers on Sunday and the House will vote on it on Wednesday.

title: White House, Republicans reach tentative debt ceiling deal
description: Key negotiators struck an agreement in principle Saturday night to extend the debt ceiling and avert a catastrophic default.
